# Design System Rules

## 1. Figma-Driven Design Tokens

### 1.1 Design Token Architecture

- **All design values MUST come from Figma**: Never hardcode colors, spacing, typography, or other design values
- **CSS Variables**: Define design tokens as CSS variables in `app/globals.css` that map directly to Figma variables
- **Hierarchical Naming**: Use Figma's naming convention: `{category}/{subcategory}/{variant}` (e.g., `base/foreground`, `spacing/8`, `text-base/leading-normal/normal`)
- **Documentation Required**: When adding new tokens, update both `app/globals.css` and create/update design analysis documentation in `specifications/`

### 1.2 Design Token Categories

*Source: Figma App-Designs, Home page (node-id=14430-88857). Convert hex via `node scripts/convert-hex-to-oklch.mjs #HEX`. Tokens use rem (16px base); run `node scripts/convert-px-to-rem.mjs app/globals.css --write` when adding new px tokens.*

**Colors**:

- `base/foreground`, `base/background`, `base/primary`, `base/primary-foreground`
- `base/border`, `base/input`, `base/muted-foreground`
- `custom/accent` for hover states
- `tailwind colors/base/black` → `#000000` → `oklch(0 0 none)`
- `tailwind colors/base/transparent` → `#ffffff00` → transparent
- Map to CSS variables: `--color-foreground`, `--color-background`, etc.

**Typography**:

- `font/font-sans` → Roboto (400, 700, 800 weights)
- `text-5xl/leading-normal/extrabold` (48px H1 desktop)
- `text-4xl/leading-normal/extrabold` (36px H1 mobile)
- `text-base/leading-normal/normal` (16px body)
- `text-sm/leading-normal/medium` (14px buttons)
- `text-xs/leading-normal/medium` → 12px / 16px line-height, weight 500

**Spacing** (in rem, 16px base):

- `spacing/0` (0), `spacing/2` (0.5rem), `spacing/3` (0.75rem), `spacing/4` (1rem), `spacing/6` (1.5rem), `spacing/8` (2rem), `spacing/10` (2.5rem), `spacing/12` (3rem), `spacing/20` (5rem)
- Use Tailwind utilities: `gap-2`, `p-4`, `gap-6`, `gap-8`

**Dimensions** (from Figma, in rem):

- `width/w-4` (1rem), `height/h-8` (2rem)
- `--touch-target-min` (2.75rem / 44px) → WCAG 2.5.5 minimum touch target

**Borders & Shadows** (1px/2px kept for crisp borders):

- `border-radius/rounded-md` (0.5rem) → `--border-radius-md`
- `shadow/xs` → `--shadow-xs` (0px 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.05))
- `shadow/sm` → `--shadow-sm` (multi-layer shadow)

**Figma Variable Reference** (Home page node 14430:88857):

| Figma Variable | Value | CSS Var |
|---------------|-------|---------|
| spacing/0 | 0 | --spacing-0 |
| spacing/2 | 0.5rem | --spacing-2 |
| spacing/3 | 0.75rem | --spacing-3 |
| spacing/4 | 1rem | --spacing-4 |
| spacing/20 | 5rem | --spacing-20-token |
| tailwind colors/base/black | oklch(0 0 none) | (use for pure black) |
| border-radius/rounded-md | 0.5rem | --border-radius-md |
| breakpoint/2xl | 1536px | --breakpoint-2xl |
| font/font-sans | Roboto | --font-roboto |
| text-xs (size/line-height) | 12px / 16px | font-size/leading |
| font-weight/medium | 500 | font-medium |

**Breakpoints** (final design):

- `breakpoint/xs` (360px max) → Smallest mobile; use `max-[360px]:` for xs-specific overrides
- `breakpoint/sm` (640px) → Mobile
- `breakpoint/md` (768px) → Tablet
- `breakpoint/lg` (1024px) → Tablet landscape
- `breakpoint/xl` (1280px) → Desktop mode switch; full nav, grid layouts enabled
- `breakpoint/2xl` (1536px) → Full desktop; inline nav, all elements visible

**3-Tier Spacing System** (Figma node 15992:29459 — applies globally):

| Tier | Breakpoints | Page padding (gutter) |
|------|-------------|----------------------|
| Tier A | xl + 2xl | 80px (5rem) |
| Tier B | md + lg | 32px (2rem) |
| Tier C | xs + sm | 28px (1.75rem) |

- Tiers share the same layout and tokens within each group
- **Layout mode switch**: `< xl` = compact mode (hamburger nav, 1-column stacking); `≥ xl` = desktop mode (full nav, grid layouts)
- Tailwind page padding utility: `px-7 md:px-8 xl:px-20`

**Responsive Typography** (3-tier system, Figma node 15992:29459):

| Element | Tier C (xs/sm) | Tier B (md/lg) | Tier A (xl/2xl) | Line-height ratio |
|---------|----------------|----------------|-----------------|-------------------|
| H1 | 36px | 48px | 60px | ~1.1–1.15 |
| H2 | 28px | 36px | 48px | ~1.15–1.25 |
| Body | 16px | 16px | 16px | 1.5 (24px) |

Tailwind utility mapping:
- `H1: text-[36px] md:text-[48px] xl:text-[60px]`
- `H2: text-[28px] md:text-[36px] xl:text-[48px]`

**Responsive Spacing** (Homepage Hero section, rem):

| Element gap | xs | sm | md | lg | xl | 2xl |
|-------------|-----|-----|-----|-----|-----|-----|
| Hero headline ↔ body | 1.25rem | 1.25rem | — | 1.25rem | 1.25rem | 2.5rem |
| Body ↔ search input | 1.5rem | 1.5rem | — | — | 2.5rem | 3.75rem |
| Search ↔ helper text | 0.5rem | 0.5rem | — | 0.5rem | 0.5rem | 0.5rem |
| Helper ↔ Explore link | 1.5rem | 1.5rem | — | — | 2.5rem | 3.75rem |
| Hero ↔ "Prefer to browse" | 4rem | 4rem | 4rem | — | 4rem | 4rem |
| Footer bottom padding | 1.75rem | 1.75rem | 1.75rem | 1.75rem | 2rem | 2rem |

**Other**: xl/2xl horizontal content padding 5rem (80px); footer column gap 1.75rem (28px). Capture from annotated Figma screenshots when analyzing new pages.

### 1.3 Using Design Tokens in Code

**In Tailwind Classes**:

```tsx
className = 'rounded-[var(--border-radius-md)]'
className = 'min-h-[120px]'
className = 'shadow-[0px_1px_2px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,0.05)]'
```

**Responsive Widths**:

```tsx
className = 'max-w-[312px] sm:max-w-[704px] lg:max-w-[604px]'
```

**DO NOT**:

- Use arbitrary pixel values without checking Figma first
- Create new spacing values that don't match the design system
- Hardcode colors as hex values in component code

