## 3. Typography System

### 3.1 Font Configuration

- **Primary Font**: Roboto via `next/font/google`
- **Weights Required**: 400 (Regular), 700 (Bold), 800 (ExtraBold for headers)
- **Variable**: `--font-roboto` applied to body element
- **Display**: `swap` for performance
- **Configuration Location**: `app/layout.tsx`

### 3.2 Font Loading

```tsx
import { Roboto } from 'next/font/google'

const roboto = Roboto({
  weight: ['400', '700', '800'],
  subsets: ['latin'],
  variable: '--font-roboto',
  display: 'swap',
})
```

### 3.3 Typography Scale

3-tier system matching the global spacing tiers (Figma node 15992:29459):

| Element | Tier A (xl/2xl) | Tier B (md/lg) | Tier C (xs/sm) | Line-height ratio | Weight          |
| ------- | --------------- | -------------- | --------------- | ----------------- | --------------- |
| H1      | 60px            | 48px           | 36px            | ~1.1–1.15         | 800 (ExtraBold) |
| H2      | 48px            | 36px           | 28px            | ~1.15–1.25        | 800 (ExtraBold) |
| Body    | 16px            | 16px           | 16px            | 1.5 (24px)        | 400 (Regular)   |
| Button  | 14px            | 14px           | 14px            | 20px              | 500 (Medium)    |
| Small   | 14px            | 14px           | 14px            | 20px              | 400 (Regular)   |

### 3.4 Implementation

```tsx
// H1 — 3-tier responsive
<h1 className="text-[36px] md:text-[48px] xl:text-[60px] font-extrabold font-['Roboto']">

// H2 — 3-tier responsive
<h2 className="text-[28px] md:text-[36px] xl:text-[48px] font-extrabold font-['Roboto']">

// Body text
<p className="text-[16px] leading-[24px] font-normal font-['Roboto']">
```

**Note**: If Roboto:ExtraBold (weight 800) is not yet loaded, add it to the font configuration.

