## 5. Responsive Design Patterns

### 5.1 Breakpoint Strategy

- **Mobile First**: Default styles target xs (≤360px) / base viewport
- **sm** (640px+): Mobile
- **md** (768px+): Tablet; header uses drawer navigation (Tier B begins)
- **lg** (1024px+): Tablet landscape
- **xl** (1280px+): **Desktop mode switch** — full nav, grid layouts enabled, Tier A begins
- **2xl** (1536px+): Full desktop; inline nav, Sign up, BizWiz visible
- **Max Width**: `max-w-screen-2xl mx-auto` container pattern
- **Page padding**: `px-7 md:px-8 xl:px-20` (28px / 32px / 80px)

### 5.2 Component Adaptations

**Header** (final design):

- xl/2xl (1280px+): Full logo (189×40px), inline nav, AGENCIES/SERVICES text, language selector, BizWiz, Sign up
- md/lg (768–1279px): Full logo, hamburger menu, language icon only
- xs/sm (≤639px): Top bar logo only; hamburger menu
- Padding: Tier A 80px · Tier B 32px · Tier C 28px

**Hero**:

- `≥ xl` (Tier A): 2-column layout (copy left, illustration right); H1 60px; padding 80px
- `md/lg` (Tier B): Stack layout (copy first); H1 48px; padding 32px
- `xs/sm` (Tier C): Stack layout; H1 36px; full-width input; action never overlaps text; padding 28px
- CTA input: xs/sm = full-width with button below or safely anchored; md+ = input + button may share row
- Hero illustration: maintain aspect ratio; allow crop; never stretch

**Footer**:

- Desktop: Horizontal layout, max-width 1280px, 96px padding
- Tablet/Mobile: Vertical stack, center-aligned, 64px padding

### 5.3 Responsive Width Pattern

```tsx
// Component-specific responsive widths
className = 'w-full max-w-[312px] sm:max-w-[704px] lg:max-w-[604px] mx-auto'
```

### 5.4 Touch vs Mouse Considerations

- **All interactive elements**: Minimum 44×44px touch target (WCAG 2.5.5)
- **Visual size can be smaller**: Use padding/margin technique (e.g., `p-1 -m-1` extends 36px to 44px)
- **Hover states**: Desktop only, skip on touch devices

