## 7. Design Analysis Documentation

### 7.1 Required Documentation

When implementing Figma designs, create a design analysis document in `specifications/{story}/`:

- **File Name**: `design-analysis-{STORY}.md`
- **Content**: Component breakdown, design tokens used, responsive behavior, Figma node IDs
- **Purpose**: Single source of truth linking Figma to code

### 7.2 Design Analysis Structure

```markdown
# Design Analysis - {STORY}: {Title}

## Design Overview

- Purpose, user flows, design system references

## Design Tokens (Extracted from Figma Variables)

- Colors, Typography, Spacing, Borders & Shadows, Breakpoints

## Component Library

- Component name, Node ID, Purpose, Variants, States, Props, Composition, Design Tokens Used, Responsive Behavior, Code Connect status

## Component States Analysis

- Default, Hover, Active, Focus, Disabled states for each component

## Responsive Design Analysis

- Breakpoint table, component adaptations, touch vs mouse

## Accessibility Considerations

- Color contrast, text sizing, focus indicators, ARIA labels, touch targets, keyboard navigation
```

### 7.3 Figma Node References

- **Always include Figma Node IDs**: Links design to implementation
- **Example**: `Node ID: 1599:15684`
- **Hover States**: Document hover state node IDs separately (e.g., `1324:23540`)

### 7.4 Accepted Deviations

When implementation differs from Figma design:

- **UI Components**: Document in [`components/ui/CUSTOMIZATIONS.md`](../components/ui/CUSTOMIZATIONS.md)
- **Other deviations**: Document in relevant specification or ADR
- **Rationale Required**: Explain why deviation is necessary
- **Examples**: shadcn/ui focus ring style, touch target trade-offs

